{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readonly","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSArray<MLNPolygon *>","preciseIdentifier":"c:Q$objc(cs)NSArray","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" * ","kind":"text"},{"text":"interiorPolygons","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The area occupied by any interior polygons is excluded from the overall shape."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Interior polygons should not overlap. An interior polygon should not have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interior polygons of its own."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If there are no interior polygons, the value of this property is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/interiorpolygons"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"interiorPolygons","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolygon(py)interiorPolygons","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The array of polygons nested inside the receiver."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon/interiorPolygons":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/interiorpolygons","title":"interiorPolygons","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"interiorPolygons","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The array of polygons nested inside the receiver.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"MapLibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","role":"collection"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the edges that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight."}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon","title":"MLNPolygon","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","role":"symbol"}}}